Roles & Responsibilities
We have a fantastic opportunity for someone to join us in the position of Business (Data) Analyst to work on our client's project, a leading global bank.
Mandatory Skill(s)
Bachelors/Masters Degree in Information Technology or Analytics or equivalent fields;
Strong experience working as an Analytics Manager or Senior Data Analyst in Data analysis and reporting;
Hands on experience in NoSQL databases, Elasticsearch (ELK) , Rest APIs , JSON, XML;
Prior experience leading a team in the analytics space;
Good Knowledge of Excel, Python , SQL and business intelligence tools (e.g. Tableau, Arcadia Data, Power BI, Kibana);
Outstanding analytical skills with excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Should be able to work in a global set up and support different business groups;
Desirable Skill(s)
Banking industry experience in infrastructure domain;
Implementation in Machine learning;
Experience in End user analytics.
Responsibilities
Responsible for gathering business requirements and developing strategies;
Configure and Implement data analytics strategies and solutions;
Extract reports from multiple sources and build systems to transform raw data into actionable items;
Lead and implement the enablement of data analytics team;
Responsible for planning, execution and to oversee operations of data analytics to ensure quality;
Continuously learning about the industry trends;
Work responsibly in a dynamic environment through leading by example and being consistent in words, actions and embedding the right behaviours.

Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE’s website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.

