Roles & Responsibilities
Job Summary
We are looking for a Data Analyst who can leverage his/her analytics skills to support automation and data analytics projects in the area of Asset Management.
Mandatory Skill-set
Degree holder majoring in Business, Finance, Computer Science or equivalent;
Experience and hands on skills in SQL, Qliksense, R, Python;
Basic proficiency in data analysis, data visualization and working with large scale datasets;
At least 2-3 years of work experience;
Team player, self­ motivated and resourceful;
Numerically inclined with a strong analytical mind;
Highly proficient in the use of Microsoft Excel and Access.
Desired Skill-set
Work Experience in Banking or Financial industry;
Familiar with Power BI/Tableau.
Responsibilities
Support Data Management team by performing data profiling, supporting data mapping specifications, data analysis, data quality check and data reconciliation;
Responsible for raw data analysis and data profiling for data integration;
Perform user acceptance testing (UAT) and create test scripts for both automated and manual testing;
Extract data from data tables in data warehouse using SQL queries;
Identify business requirements and provide technical documentation;
Able to manage delivery of projects through complete SDLC;
Provide post implementation support, investigating data issues and queries;
Participating in providing support for SIT/UAT.
Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.
When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE’s website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).
Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.
